The paper discusses the use of Artificial Intelligence for intrusion detection and response, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper specifically focuses on the lack of explainability and interpretability of AI models, which suggests a focus on explainable AI (cs.AI). The infusion of domain knowledge also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the mention of IoT devices suggests a focus on sensor networks (cs.SI).
